1
00:01:32,640 --> 00:01:35,040
=Love Again=

2
00:01:35,300 --> 00:01:38,110
=Episode 3=

3
00:01:38,430 --> 00:01:41,030
Didn't you touch her hand?

4
00:01:42,111 --> 00:01:43,030
Keep your voice down.

5
00:01:44,200 --> 00:01:45,600
I told you to keep your voice down.

6
00:01:47,670 --> 00:01:49,740
With my body and my age,

7
00:01:50,510 --> 00:01:51,150
forget it.

8
00:01:52,460 --> 00:01:53,740
You think about your age now?

9
00:01:54,030 --> 00:01:55,620
You were 17 when you touched her hand.

10
00:01:55,844 --> 00:01:57,670
Now that you let go,
you are 70 years old.

11
00:01:57,790 --> 00:01:59,310
Don't be such a loser, will you?

12
00:02:00,310 --> 00:02:02,070
Self-awareness is a valuable trait.

13
00:02:02,510 --> 00:02:03,380
Besides, I think...

14
00:02:04,380 --> 00:02:05,980
I think Shen Qing and Lina

15
00:02:06,200 --> 00:02:07,755
aren't particularly supportive of it.

16
00:02:07,820 --> 00:02:08,310
Shen.

17
00:02:08,900 --> 00:02:10,620
Taking good care of yourself

18
00:02:11,710 --> 00:02:13,940
is the best support
you can give your children.

19
00:02:14,177 --> 00:02:15,133
Think about it.

20
00:02:15,550 --> 00:02:17,710
If you take Ms. Lian home,

21
00:02:18,030 --> 00:02:20,500
won't the whole family
welcome her with open arms?

22
00:02:20,800 --> 00:02:21,500
I'm telling you.

23
00:02:21,660 --> 00:02:22,940
Tomorrow is your last chance.

24
00:02:23,711 --> 00:02:24,644
Confess to her.

25
00:02:24,740 --> 00:02:25,660
Let the secret out.

26
00:02:27,060 --> 00:02:27,340
Con...

27
00:02:29,150 --> 00:02:29,900
Confess?

28
00:02:31,310 --> 00:02:32,830
Isn't that too fast?

29
00:02:33,590 --> 00:02:35,220
Look at you dawdling.

30
00:02:35,340 --> 00:02:37,180
Do you want to be single forever?

31
00:02:37,180 --> 00:02:38,060
Keep your voice down.

32
00:02:38,060 --> 00:02:39,180
Don't be so mad. Come on.

33
00:02:40,150 --> 00:02:40,660
Sit.

34
00:02:45,550 --> 00:02:45,870
How...

35
00:02:47,030 --> 00:02:48,460
How should I confess my feelings?

36
00:02:55,844 --> 00:02:57,622
I think you should sing a song for her.

37
00:02:58,390 --> 00:02:58,940
Sing a song?

38
00:03:00,590 --> 00:03:01,430
I can't sing.

39
00:03:01,990 --> 00:03:03,110
Reciting a poem is my forte.

40
00:03:03,110 --> 00:03:03,500
Fine.

41
00:03:04,060 --> 00:03:06,390
Shen, please don't recite a poem.

42
00:03:06,400 --> 00:03:08,440
Have you forgotten
about the Mid-Autumn Festival party?

43
00:03:08,444 --> 00:03:10,760
Didn't you land yourself in the hospital
with your recital?

44
00:03:11,110 --> 00:03:11,590
Fine.

45
00:03:11,590 --> 00:03:12,180
Enough of this.

46
00:03:12,270 --> 00:03:13,150
Let's sing then.

47
00:03:15,444 --> 00:03:17,555
Poems express intent,
while songs perpetuate words.

48
00:03:17,900 --> 00:03:18,500
Let's sing...

49
00:03:19,666 --> 00:03:20,710
What song should I sing?

50
00:03:22,870 --> 00:03:25,060
Why don't you sing the song
when I confessed my love?

51
00:03:25,550 --> 00:03:26,110
"Wildflowers".

52
00:03:26,780 --> 00:03:27,500
Let me tell you.

53
00:03:28,022 --> 00:03:29,310
As soon as I finished singing,

54
00:03:29,740 --> 00:03:32,780
Tianzhen agreed immediately.

55
00:03:34,620 --> 00:03:35,460
Is it that magical?

56
00:03:36,620 --> 00:03:37,220
Wildflowers?

57
00:03:37,955 --> 00:03:38,955
How do you sing it?

58
00:03:39,000 --> 00:03:39,911
Give me a minute.

59
00:03:40,310 --> 00:03:41,150
Let me show you.

60
00:03:54,060 --> 00:03:56,780
♪For whom
do wildflowers on the mountain♪

61
00:03:56,780 --> 00:03:59,150
♪Bloom and fade?♪

62
00:03:59,632 --> 00:04:05,460
♪Waiting quietly to see
if someone will pick them♪

63
00:04:05,533 --> 00:04:06,890
The lyrics are quite well written.

64
00:04:06,897 --> 00:04:12,287
♪Just like that flower,
I wait for his arrival♪

65
00:04:14,460 --> 00:04:16,860
Mom, I think Lian Yilian is quite good.

66
00:04:17,150 --> 00:04:18,070
She's friendly.

67
00:04:18,900 --> 00:04:19,980
She's even the head nurse.

68
00:04:20,340 --> 00:04:22,390
A hospital remains unchanging,

69
00:04:22,444 --> 00:04:23,950
but patients come and go frequently.

70
00:04:24,200 --> 00:04:26,711
Right? There are many people
who are better and younger

71
00:04:27,070 --> 00:04:28,830
than your father-in-law.

72
00:04:29,390 --> 00:04:30,420
A head nurse?

73
00:04:32,220 --> 00:04:34,540
Why is she still single?

74
00:04:35,780 --> 00:04:38,860
I heard it was because
she had to take care of her son.

75
00:04:39,630 --> 00:04:40,030
Son?

76
00:04:40,030 --> 00:04:41,340
Her son wasn't in good health.

77
00:04:44,540 --> 00:04:45,070
Her son.

78
00:04:45,950 --> 00:04:49,220
A son with poor health is scarier
than one who lives off his parents.

79
00:04:49,860 --> 00:04:51,100
Right? She...

80
00:04:52,460 --> 00:04:53,460
- I'll leave.
- Go.

81
00:04:53,460 --> 00:04:54,955
- Go play for a while.
- I'll leave.

82
00:04:55,022 --> 00:04:55,822
Go play for a while.

83
00:04:57,710 --> 00:04:58,390
I'm telling you.

84
00:04:58,900 --> 00:05:00,830
She must have other intentions.

85
00:05:02,070 --> 00:05:03,950
Mom, you're doing it again.

86
00:05:03,950 --> 00:05:06,070
Is there now truth, goodness, and beauty
in the world?

87
00:05:06,070 --> 00:05:07,270
Goodness and beauty.

88
00:05:07,270 --> 00:05:08,155
I'm leaving then.

89
00:05:08,200 --> 00:05:08,844
I'm telling you.

90
00:05:08,844 --> 00:05:11,400
Let me know when your father-in-law
is discharged from the hospital.

91
00:05:11,400 --> 00:05:13,150
We'll get prepared, handle it swiftly,

92
00:05:13,460 --> 00:05:14,980
and cut off all possibilities.

93
00:05:18,460 --> 00:05:18,830
Mom.

94
00:05:19,066 --> 00:05:20,400
I left an exercise book at school.

95
00:05:20,400 --> 00:05:21,529
I have to go back and get it.

96
00:05:21,530 --> 00:05:22,880
Why didn't you stay at school?

97
00:05:22,888 --> 00:05:24,155
I need to rush home to cook.

98
00:05:24,270 --> 00:05:25,900
Didn't you take me away?

99
00:05:26,133 --> 00:05:27,911
I'll take the subway and be back soon.

100
00:05:28,300 --> 00:05:29,270
Be careful.

101
00:05:29,355 --> 00:05:30,888
- Got it.
- Watch out for the cars!

102
00:05:33,660 --> 00:05:35,390
Lian, bed two has finished the IV drip.

103
00:05:36,540 --> 00:05:36,780
Okay.

104
00:05:36,780 --> 00:05:39,710
Lian, have you read the apology letter
from the family member who made a scene?

105
00:05:39,710 --> 00:05:40,980
We've gotten justice.

106
00:05:41,220 --> 00:05:41,860
Yay.

107
00:05:44,270 --> 00:05:44,750
Lin.

108
00:05:45,750 --> 00:05:46,300
Well...

109
00:05:46,830 --> 00:05:48,950
I have something to do on Tuesday.

110
00:05:49,355 --> 00:05:50,622
Can I switch shifts with you?

111
00:05:50,830 --> 00:05:51,660
Sure.

112
00:05:52,510 --> 00:05:52,950
Thanks.

113
00:05:54,822 --> 00:05:56,822
Professor Shen
is getting discharged on Tuesday.

114
00:05:56,888 --> 00:05:58,666
Are you
not going to bid goodbye to him?

115
00:05:58,950 --> 00:05:59,420
No need.

116
00:06:06,761 --> 00:06:12,557
♪For whom do wildflowers on the mountain
bloom and fade♪

117
00:06:13,351 --> 00:06:16,651
♪Waiting quietly to see
if someone will pick them♪

118
00:06:16,710 --> 00:06:17,150
Grandpa.

119
00:06:19,540 --> 00:06:20,390
Why are you here?

120
00:06:20,830 --> 00:06:22,220
I'm here to see you, Grandpa.

121
00:06:22,220 --> 00:06:23,950
Will you be discharged
the day after tomorrow?

122
00:06:23,955 --> 00:06:25,111
Yes, sit down.

123
00:06:27,900 --> 00:06:28,300
Grandpa.

124
00:06:30,540 --> 00:06:32,270
Is Ms. Lian your girlfriend now?

125
00:06:35,900 --> 00:06:36,220
No.

126
00:06:36,533 --> 00:06:37,488
Don't talk nonsense.

127
00:06:37,860 --> 00:06:38,340
No.

128
00:06:39,750 --> 00:06:40,070
You...

129
00:06:41,190 --> 00:06:42,100
You haven't confessed?

130
00:06:43,190 --> 00:06:43,750
No.

131
00:06:44,750 --> 00:06:45,300
Grandpa.

132
00:06:46,070 --> 00:06:47,340
Didn't you tell me

133
00:06:47,400 --> 00:06:49,540
that courage is the greatest quality
of a human being?

134
00:06:49,980 --> 00:06:51,150
You got to be brave.

135
00:06:56,422 --> 00:06:58,311
I was going to give this
to someone else.

136
00:06:58,333 --> 00:06:59,644
I'll let you use it first.

137
00:06:59,780 --> 00:07:00,390
Take it.

138
00:07:09,190 --> 00:07:09,860
Who is it for?

139
00:07:11,150 --> 00:07:11,540
Don't ask.

140
00:07:11,800 --> 00:07:13,190
I won't tell you even if you ask me.

141
00:07:15,190 --> 00:07:15,590
Grandpa.

142
00:07:15,630 --> 00:07:17,270
I'll tell you when you succeed.

143
00:07:20,390 --> 00:07:22,340
You have secrets now.

144
00:07:27,340 --> 00:07:27,780
Grandpa.

145
00:07:28,800 --> 00:07:30,030
Grandma appeared in my dream.

146
00:07:30,780 --> 00:07:31,630
She told me

147
00:07:32,590 --> 00:07:34,540
she came into this world with nothing

148
00:07:34,666 --> 00:07:36,510
and took a lot of love with her
when she left.

149
00:07:37,420 --> 00:07:38,300
She's satisfied.

150
00:07:42,510 --> 00:07:43,780
She wants to thank you,

151
00:07:44,420 --> 00:07:45,420
but she's shy.

152
00:07:49,710 --> 00:07:50,860
Because we Chinese always say

153
00:07:50,860 --> 00:07:53,200
that family members
don't need to be formal with each other.

154
00:07:54,070 --> 00:07:54,390
Yes.

155
00:07:54,390 --> 00:07:55,780
But she still has to say it.

156
00:07:56,390 --> 00:07:57,150
Otherwise,

157
00:08:01,150 --> 00:08:03,340
how will you know
she gave you a five-star rating?

158
00:08:07,900 --> 00:08:08,300
Really?

159
00:08:09,390 --> 00:08:10,190
Of course.

160
00:08:11,390 --> 00:08:12,220
Tell me

161
00:08:12,220 --> 00:08:13,390
what else did Grandma say?

162
00:08:15,660 --> 00:08:16,590
Grandma also asked you

163
00:08:16,688 --> 00:08:19,488
to love the sunshine on sunny days
and love the rain on rainy days.

164
00:08:24,340 --> 00:08:24,780
Grandpa.

165
00:08:27,377 --> 00:08:28,630
Grandma wants you to be happy.

166
00:08:33,350 --> 00:08:35,900
You're quite a smooth talker.

167
00:08:41,700 --> 00:08:43,750
Lide Pharmaceutical has a patent

168
00:08:44,230 --> 00:08:45,390
called NPI.

169
00:08:45,900 --> 00:08:47,940
Dr. Qin suggested that we bring it in.

170
00:08:49,973 --> 00:08:51,380
(Shen Dai)

171
00:08:52,470 --> 00:08:52,820
Go on.

172
00:08:54,060 --> 00:08:56,780
This is a tumor blood vessel disruptor.

173
00:08:57,470 --> 00:08:59,180
It's effective

174
00:08:59,350 --> 00:09:01,300
for our M701 and M703 targeted drugs.

175
00:09:01,870 --> 00:09:03,180
If the introduction is successful,

176
00:09:03,540 --> 00:09:05,870
it will greatly accelerate
our research and development.

177
00:09:06,266 --> 00:09:07,470
It's almost time to start work.

178
00:09:07,470 --> 00:09:10,230
I'll ask Jin to send an email
to inquire about the price.

179
00:09:11,510 --> 00:09:12,990
Because there are many companies

180
00:09:12,990 --> 00:09:14,030
eyeing this patent.

181
00:09:14,150 --> 00:09:15,540
So we must hurry up.

182
00:09:15,660 --> 00:09:18,350
If you have any specialized inquiries,

183
00:09:18,540 --> 00:09:19,870
consult Dr. Qin.

184
00:09:19,933 --> 00:09:21,470
If you have any questions, just ask me.

185
00:09:21,733 --> 00:09:23,150
I'll go work on my experiment first.

186
00:09:23,150 --> 00:09:23,820
Okay, thank you.

187
00:09:23,844 --> 00:09:25,400
- Dr. Qin, thank you.
- It's okay.

188
00:09:29,111 --> 00:09:31,350
I was embarrassed to say
when the scientist was here.

189
00:09:31,780 --> 00:09:33,510
About the price...

190
00:09:33,780 --> 00:09:34,660
Don't worry.

191
00:09:34,780 --> 00:09:35,780
I'll ask the finance team

192
00:09:35,780 --> 00:09:37,350
to calculate the cost-effectiveness.

193
00:09:37,644 --> 00:09:40,059
It's a good thing
that I recruited you from the Big Four.

194
00:09:40,060 --> 00:09:41,090
Otherwise, what would I do?

195
00:09:41,150 --> 00:09:42,400
Stop making random confessions.

196
00:09:43,150 --> 00:09:44,780
Alright, go home. It's getting late.

197
00:09:45,350 --> 00:09:46,230
Go home?

198
00:09:46,288 --> 00:09:47,800
My dad will be discharged.

199
00:09:47,911 --> 00:09:49,470
I have a lot of work to do.

200
00:09:50,100 --> 00:09:50,933
I'll go back to work.

201
00:09:50,955 --> 00:09:52,133
Don't exhaust yourself.

202
00:09:52,177 --> 00:09:53,180
You should hurry home.

203
00:09:53,540 --> 00:09:54,540
I have plans tonight.

204
00:09:55,200 --> 00:09:56,666
Take good care of yourself.

205
00:09:58,957 --> 00:10:02,402
(Inpatient)

206
00:10:03,230 --> 00:10:05,900
♪Pat me on the shoulder, and I'll...♪

207
00:10:06,510 --> 00:10:09,230
♪Do whatever you say♪

208
00:10:09,780 --> 00:10:12,580
♪Swaying flowers♪

209
00:10:13,390 --> 00:10:16,230
♪She needs your comfort too♪

210
00:10:16,750 --> 00:10:17,750
♪Don't let her...♪

211
00:10:19,390 --> 00:10:21,900
♪Grow old and wither♪

212
00:10:23,600 --> 00:10:25,700
It's time to get off work, Ms. Lian.
I got to go.

213
00:10:26,300 --> 00:10:26,630
Okay.

214
00:10:33,820 --> 00:10:39,750
For whom do wildflowers on the mountain
bloom and fade...

215
00:10:40,270 --> 00:10:46,270
♪Waiting quietly to see
if someone will pick them♪

216
00:11:00,940 --> 00:11:01,420
Yilian.

217
00:11:04,750 --> 00:11:05,540
I'm old

218
00:11:06,990 --> 00:11:07,750
and in poor health.

219
00:11:09,940 --> 00:11:11,110
God arranged for me

220
00:11:12,750 --> 00:11:14,900
to be hospitalized here
so that I could meet you.

221
00:11:15,940 --> 00:11:16,870
I can't let God down.

222
00:11:18,420 --> 00:11:19,700
I...

223
00:11:19,900 --> 00:11:21,940
I wrote an acrostic poem for you.

224
00:11:24,660 --> 00:11:26,470
Listen to the rain under the roof.

225
00:11:28,540 --> 00:11:30,420
You're as beautiful
as tomorrow's flower.

226
00:11:31,900 --> 00:11:33,780
Lone figure on a spring night.

227
00:11:35,230 --> 00:11:37,900
I want to confess to you my secret.

228
00:11:42,750 --> 00:11:45,180
I now change "My secret"
to "Until we grow old together".

229
00:11:46,300 --> 00:11:49,630
I want to confess to you
until we grow old together.

230
00:11:53,990 --> 00:11:55,820
I want to be with you.

231
00:11:59,180 --> 00:12:00,580
Let's be together as long as we can.

232
00:12:18,870 --> 00:12:20,150
Chocolates from my grandson.

233
00:12:21,270 --> 00:12:22,350
There are even chocolates.

234
00:12:40,900 --> 00:12:41,900
I'll apply some glue

235
00:12:42,390 --> 00:12:43,270
on this handrail.

236
00:12:43,820 --> 00:12:44,700
Your father can use it

237
00:12:45,200 --> 00:12:46,333
when he comes home tomorrow.

238
00:12:46,660 --> 00:12:47,300
Shen Qing.

239
00:12:47,900 --> 00:12:48,300
Shen Qing.

240
00:12:48,300 --> 00:12:48,750
Look.

241
00:12:50,580 --> 00:12:52,060
Set an alarm on my phone.

242
00:12:52,580 --> 00:12:53,270
The doctor said

243
00:12:53,270 --> 00:12:55,750
your father has several medicines
that he has to take on time.

244
00:12:55,940 --> 00:12:57,300
What time should I set?

245
00:12:57,470 --> 00:12:58,700
Two are before dinner.

246
00:12:58,750 --> 00:12:59,660
Two are after dinner.

247
00:12:59,660 --> 00:13:00,110
Here?

248
00:13:00,300 --> 00:13:00,940
Yes.

249
00:13:02,420 --> 00:13:03,110
Is it my dad?

250
00:13:03,110 --> 00:13:09,110
♪For whom do wildflowers on the mountain
bloom and fade...♪

251
00:13:09,110 --> 00:13:10,110
How come you're back?

252
00:13:10,110 --> 00:13:11,420
Weren't you going home on Tuesday?

253
00:13:11,420 --> 00:13:12,230
That's right, Dad.

254
00:13:12,288 --> 00:13:13,750
I'll get discharged when I recover.

255
00:13:13,750 --> 00:13:15,460
What difference
does Monday or Tuesday make?

256
00:13:15,466 --> 00:13:16,640
It's not a good place, right?

257
00:13:16,640 --> 00:13:18,180
Shen Duole, what's going on?

258
00:13:24,577 --> 00:13:25,750
What's that supposed to mean?

259
00:13:25,940 --> 00:13:26,870
What gestures are those?

260
00:13:27,630 --> 00:13:28,150
Fine.

261
00:13:28,510 --> 00:13:29,630
I'll explain.

262
00:13:30,870 --> 00:13:31,230
In-laws.

263
00:13:32,660 --> 00:13:34,110
Ever since Jingmin died,

264
00:13:34,700 --> 00:13:35,780
I've been depressed.

265
00:13:37,230 --> 00:13:38,700
Today, I took the first step

266
00:13:39,390 --> 00:13:41,660
to express my feelings to Ms. Lian.

267
00:13:43,700 --> 00:13:44,900
Duole said it well.

268
00:13:45,630 --> 00:13:46,780
Duole told me

269
00:13:46,820 --> 00:13:48,230
to love the sunshine on sunny days

270
00:13:48,444 --> 00:13:49,844
and love the rain on rainy days.

271
00:13:50,270 --> 00:13:51,350
What was I like in the past?

272
00:13:52,180 --> 00:13:53,660
I was afraid of the sun on sunny days

273
00:13:53,711 --> 00:13:55,644
and scared of getting wet on rainy days.

274
00:13:56,060 --> 00:13:58,630
I want to change
my attitude toward life.

275
00:13:59,780 --> 00:14:00,700
I get it now.

276
00:14:01,580 --> 00:14:03,030
If I live my life well,

277
00:14:03,110 --> 00:14:05,510
it will be the greatest support
for my children.

278
00:14:07,150 --> 00:14:07,660
And you,

279
00:14:07,870 --> 00:14:08,350
Baoqin.

280
00:14:08,870 --> 00:14:09,870
I remember the shoes.

281
00:14:10,177 --> 00:14:11,911
You don't need Shen Qin to buy them now.

282
00:14:11,933 --> 00:14:13,150
I know how to order online now.

283
00:14:13,270 --> 00:14:14,270
Just wait for delivery.

284
00:14:19,470 --> 00:14:21,420
By the way,
I would like to solemnly say this.

285
00:14:23,270 --> 00:14:24,750
During my time in hospital,

286
00:14:25,820 --> 00:14:27,580
you all have been busy running around

287
00:14:28,420 --> 00:14:29,300
and worried.

288
00:14:30,940 --> 00:14:32,060
You guys worked hard.

289
00:14:33,700 --> 00:14:34,510
Thank you.

290
00:14:36,700 --> 00:14:37,470
Thank you all.

291
00:14:39,900 --> 00:14:40,420
Dad, you...

292
00:14:40,900 --> 00:14:41,750
Dad, well...

293
00:14:47,730 --> 00:14:53,570
♪For whom do wildflowers on the mountain
bloom and fade♪

294
00:14:54,340 --> 00:14:57,105
♪Waiting quietly to see
if someone will pick them♪

295
00:14:57,230 --> 00:14:57,900
Shen Dai.

296
00:14:59,180 --> 00:14:59,580
Lina.

297
00:15:00,300 --> 00:15:02,750
